content:
### CSS Grid Gap

**gap** controls spacing between grid cells.

---

### Gap Properties

```css
.container {
  display: grid;
  gap: 20px;              /* Both row and column */
  row-gap: 10px;          /* Row spacing only */
  column-gap: 20px;       /* Column spacing only */
}
```

---

### Row Gap

```css
.container {
  grid-template-rows: 1fr 1fr 1fr;
  row-gap: 30px;
}
/* 30px vertical space between rows */
```

---

### Column Gap

```css
.container {
  grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
  column-gap: 20px;
}
/* 20px horizontal space between columns */
```

---

### Gap Shorthand

```css
/* One value - same for rows and columns */
gap: 20px;

/* Two values - row column */
gap: 10px 30px;
```

---

### Gap vs Margin

| Gap | Margin |
|-----|--------|
| Applied to container | Applied to items |
| Only between items | Also on outer edges |
| Cleaner syntax | Can be negative |
| No collapsing | Collapses vertically |

```css
/* Using gap */
.container { display: grid; gap: 20px; }

/* Same with margin */
.item { margin: 10px; }
/* But adds 10px on outer edges too */
```

---

### Gap and Grid Functions

```css
.container {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
  gap: 15px;
  padding: 20px;
}
```

---

### Old vs Modern Syntax

| Old (deprecated) | Modern |
|-----------------|--------|
| `grid-gap` | `gap` |
| `grid-row-gap` | `row-gap` |
| `grid-column-gap` | `column-gap` |

---

> **Best Practice:** Always use `gap` instead of margins on grid items. It's cleaner and doesn't create edge spacing issues.
